+---
+type: protocol
+authority: A3_OPERATIONAL_DRAFT
+status: DRAFT_NON_PRODUCTION
+schema_id: ion.carrier_friction_ledger_protocol.v0
+created: 2026-05-07
+production_authority: false
+live_execution_authority: false
+---
+
+# ION Carrier Friction Ledger Protocol v0
+
+## Purpose
+
+The Carrier Friction Ledger captures avoidable friction encountered by an ION
+carrier while performing bounded work.
+
+A friction event is not automatically a bug and not automatically accepted
+state. It is improvement evidence: a structured observation that the carrier had
+to spend attention on substrate ambiguity, missing context, unclear authority,
+tool instability, response shape, proof obligations, or human-relay burden that
+ION may be able to reduce.
+
+## Core law
+
+```text
+Avoidable carrier inference is improvement evidence.
+```
+
+When a carrier must infer workflow law, authority, context, proof obligations,
+transport state, active package boundaries, or next lawful action, ION should log
+that inference burden as a candidate substrate repair.
+
+## Non-goals
+
+This protocol does not require or permit raw chain-of-thought disclosure.
+
+Record structured workflow facts only:
+
+- what happened
+- why it mattered
+- what inference or workaround was required
+- what missing precondition would have made the next move obvious
+- what fix class should receive the event
+
+Do not record secrets, credentials, private hidden reasoning, or unbounded user
+data.
+
+## Event storage
+
+Default draft storage:
+
+```text
+ION/05_context/current/carrier_friction/events/
+ION/05_context/current/carrier_friction/ACTIVE_CARRIER_FRICTION_LEDGER.json
+```
+
+Events are evidence until Steward/human review classifies them.
+
+## Severity
+
+```text
+S0_OBSERVATION              useful note, no active workflow burden
+S1_MINOR                    minor wording or UX issue
+S2_WORKFLOW_FRICTION        avoidable inference or retry; work continued
+S3_BLOCKING                 work blocked or required human rescue/workaround
+S4_STATE_RISK               could cause false readiness, wrong state, stale inheritance, duplicate mutation, or missing receipt
+S5_SAFETY_AUTHORITY_RISK    touches production, live execution, secrets, deletion, deployment, or hard-gated authority
+```
+
+## Minimum fields
+
+See `ION/03_registry/carrier_friction_event_schema.yaml`.
+
+## Steward dispositions
+
+```text
+new
+duplicate
+accepted_issue
+rejected
+escalated
+converted_to_codex_packet
+fixed
+```
+
+## Relationship to existing telemetry
+
+This ledger is not a replacement for expressive telemetry, core system
+telemetry, action receipts, or deep operational cartography. It is a specific
+improvement loop for carrier friction and inference debt.
+
+## Lifecycle
+
+```text
+carrier observes friction
+→ event is recorded
+→ recurrence fingerprint deduplicates repeated pain
+→ Steward classifies event
+→ severe or repeated events become Codex work packets, tests, context fixes, tool fixes, template fixes, or package/UX fixes
+→ receipt records accepted repair
+```
+
+## Non-authority boundary
+
+This protocol grants no production authority, live execution authority,
+credential access, delete authority, git push authority, or direct acceptance of
+unproofed worker output.

